creator: rainer.jung@kippdata.de
text:
I suspect this is a duplicate of issue https://issues.apache.org/bugzilla/show_bug.cgi?id=55789 although the symptoms differ slightly. It could be that you have old Apache headers installed in the default search path and that they shadow the new one. For instance check whether you find httpd.h in /usr/local/include. If so, than read the other ticket and either clean up /usr/local/include or read and follow comment #7 in the other issue.

Please report back here so that we might close this one here as a duplicate of 55789.

Regards,

Rainer

That was it.  I backed up the /usr/local/include/http* files, removed them, and re-ran the compile and all built ok:

www# ./apachectl -v
Server version: Apache/2.4.7 (Unix)
Server built:   Nov 28 2013 10:31:11


Thank you very much
